# 📌 Summary

Enterprise Java evolved over three decades.

Each generation solved problems from the previous one.

Spring became the industry standard because it dramatically simplified enterprise application development.

Spring Boot further accelerated development by removing repetitive configuration.

Understanding this evolution helps explain why modern Java backend development is centered around Spring Boot.

